    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-03-20T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-03-20T08:00:00-05:00" n="216"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d216">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/2957: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Paraguay</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wheeler</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Asunción</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-03-20T09:00:00-04:00"
                            >March 20, 1933—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 11:35 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>36. Yesterday Uruguay inquired confidentially whether Paraguay would receive from
                    that Government an independent proposal for an armistice the main features of
                    which proposal were indicated. Ayala replied that Paraguay’s engagement with the
                    ABCP would forbid its consideration at the present time. He tells me that the
                    contemplated proposal was of such a character that he has no idea it could be
                    made acceptable. Yesterday by instruction of their Governments the Chilean and
                    Brazilian Ministers here appealed to him not to declare a state of war. He
                    answered that in view of the continued passage of armament for Bolivia,
                    Paraguay’s only recourse was to invoke the law of neutrality.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wheeler</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
